50:40.560 --> 50:43.440
Anyway, let's go back to talking about Sigmund Freud.

50:43.680 --> 50:45.280
The mother half took over completely.

50:53.440 --> 50:54.640
Do I look okay?

50:54.640 --> 50:55.760
Is my hat on straight?

50:56.480 --> 51:01.120
So we keep running into this avoidance of the word envy.

51:01.120 --> 51:04.000
And people especially cannot seem to notice

51:04.000 --> 51:06.560
when they themselves are feeling envious.

51:06.560 --> 51:09.920
Like that person who puzzled over the angry resentful feeling

51:09.920 --> 51:11.120
in the pit of their stomach

51:11.120 --> 51:13.600
without being able to name what they were feeling.

51:13.600 --> 51:15.920
There's two reasons why people are usually in denial

51:15.920 --> 51:17.120
about their own envy.

51:17.120 --> 51:19.280
One is guilt, and the other is shame.

51:20.240 --> 51:20.740
Shame.

51:21.200 --> 51:24.800
Shame because admitting to yourself that you envy someone

51:24.800 --> 51:27.520
implies that you feel inferior to them,

51:27.520 --> 51:28.720
which is shameful.

51:28.720 --> 51:30.400
It wounds the ego.

51:30.400 --> 51:33.440
And guilt because envy is malicious.

51:33.440 --> 51:36.720
If you envy someone, you may feel angry and miserable

51:36.720 --> 51:38.880
about their success and good fortune,

51:38.880 --> 51:41.840
and you may wish to see them ruined or brought down.

51:41.840 --> 51:44.080
That's cruel and antisocial.

51:44.080 --> 51:46.480
It goes against most ideas of morality,

51:46.480 --> 51:48.160
and it's a thought that's usually

51:48.160 --> 51:50.480
not socially acceptable to admit.

51:50.480 --> 51:55.040
So envy is shameful, guilty, and socially unacceptable.

51:55.040 --> 51:58.720
And we deal with that by suppressing it from our awareness.

51:58.720 --> 52:00.240
But it is still there.

52:00.240 --> 52:02.400
And in order to maintain the denial,

52:02.400 --> 52:06.160
we have to convince ourselves that this angry resentful feeling

52:06.160 --> 52:09.680
in the pit of our stomach is actually something else.

52:09.680 --> 52:11.680
Think about how in Spongebob,

52:11.680 --> 52:15.360
Squidward shows contempt for Spongebob's childishness,

52:15.360 --> 52:18.240
for blowing bubbles, for having fun at work,

52:18.240 --> 52:22.800
when in fact, Squidward envies Spongebob's uninhibited joy

52:22.800 --> 52:24.480
and intuitive creativity.

52:24.480 --> 52:26.960
But he can't allow himself to have the thought

52:26.960 --> 52:28.720
that he envies Spongebob,

52:28.720 --> 52:30.640
because that would mean recognizing

52:30.640 --> 52:33.040
the intolerably shameful truth

52:33.120 --> 52:36.000
that he feels inferior to Spongebob.

52:36.000 --> 52:38.240
So what he does instead is convince himself

52:38.240 --> 52:41.840
that what he really is, is a refined sophisticate,

52:41.840 --> 52:44.080
scoffing at this childish fool.

52:44.080 --> 52:47.680
How did I ever get surrounded by such loser neighbors?

52:49.680 --> 52:53.200
We could call this envy-to-contempt sublimation.

52:53.200 --> 52:56.080
Sublimation is a psychoanalytic term,

52:56.080 --> 52:59.520
which means that you transform an ego-wounding feeling

52:59.520 --> 53:01.440
or socially unacceptable longing

53:02.080 --> 53:05.600
into something more ego-flattering or socially acceptable.

53:05.600 --> 53:08.000
So the classic example used by Freud

53:08.000 --> 53:10.560
is the transformation of sexual urges,

53:10.560 --> 53:14.240
of erotic energy, into creative expression.

53:14.240 --> 53:16.480
It's like the founder of the NoFap movement,

53:16.480 --> 53:18.160
Lady Gaga, once said,

53:18.160 --> 53:20.720
I have this weird thing that if I sleep with someone,

53:20.720 --> 53:23.040
they're gonna take my creativity from me through my...

53:23.920 --> 53:25.200
So according to Freud,

53:25.200 --> 53:28.080
the vast majority of erotic longings

53:28.080 --> 53:29.600
can never be fulfilled.

53:29.600 --> 53:30.960
Tell me about a segment...

53:30.960 --> 53:32.480
Ugh, misery.

53:33.120 --> 53:35.680
But there's a positive side to this, supposedly,

53:35.680 --> 53:38.720
which is that you can sublimate your erotic longings

53:38.720 --> 53:41.520
into a more socially acceptable productivity.

53:41.520 --> 53:43.840
So, you know, instead of slicking the bean,

53:43.840 --> 53:47.280
maybe you write novels about thirsty vampires,

53:47.280 --> 53:49.680
or for that matter, philosophical treatises

53:49.680 --> 53:50.880
about the will to power.

53:50.880 --> 53:52.400
Oh, we'll get to you.

53:52.400 --> 53:54.640
Freud thought that civilization itself

53:54.640 --> 53:56.800
is built at the cost of our instincts,

53:56.800 --> 53:58.960
most of which we have to sacrifice

53:58.960 --> 54:00.640
in order to live in a society.

54:00.640 --> 54:02.560
So like erotic impulses,

54:02.560 --> 54:04.720
I think envy can be sublimated,

54:04.720 --> 54:07.520
which is what's happening when it becomes contempt.

54:07.520 --> 54:10.480
Another example is the blog McMansion Hell,

54:10.480 --> 54:12.800
which makes fun of the tasteless architecture

54:12.800 --> 54:15.200
of suburban ostentatious trash.

54:15.200 --> 54:18.000
I would argue that part of the fun of this blog

54:18.000 --> 54:23.200
is the pleasure and relief of looking down at the rich.

54:23.200 --> 54:25.760
Because looking enviously up at the rich

54:25.760 --> 54:28.800
is painful, it makes you feel inferior.

54:28.800 --> 54:30.800
And a way to alleviate that pain

54:30.800 --> 54:33.360
is to sublimate envy and pretend

54:33.360 --> 54:35.840
that you're an aristocratic aesthete

54:35.840 --> 54:39.440
scoffing at the vulgar taste of the era of East.

54:39.440 --> 54:43.520
These flying buttresses are an extremely poor taste.

54:43.520 --> 54:46.800
